(66, 61, 'Peoples University of Bangladesh', 'PUB', 'Professor Dr. A.K.M Salahuddin', '3/2, Block-A Asad Avenue, Mohammadpur Dhaka-1207', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF+%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%B8+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF+%E0%A6%85%E0%A6%AC+%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%82%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6/@23.7603863,90.3701703,21z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x3755bf55d402303d:0x4d1a4d3fa2302169!8m2!3d23.7602386!4d90.3703339', 'pub.jfif', 'pep.jpg', 'Mr. Md. Shirajul Islam Mollah, MP', '', 'blank-profile-picture-973460_960_720.png', 'Professor Dr. A.K.M Salahuddin', '', 'blank-profile-picture-973460_960_720.png'),
(67, 60, 'North East University Bangladesh', 'NEUB', 'Professor Dr. Atful Hye Shibly', 'Sheikhghat - Kazirbazar Rd, Sylhet 3100', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A5+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF+%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%82%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6/@24.890232,91.8607309,20.5z/data=!4m12!1m6!3m5!1s0x3751aacd70cd7665:0xc8ae330ad72490dd!2z4Kao4Kaw4KeN4KalIOCmh-CmuOCnjeCmnyDgpofgpongpqjgpr_gpq3gpr7gprDgp43gprjgpr_gpp_gpr8g4Kas4Ka-4KaC4Kay4Ka-4Kam4KeH4Ka2!8m2!', 'neub.jfif', 'd382bd8ae87d9139df6458192532657c_L.jpg', 'Adv. Iqbal Ahmed Chowdhury', 'We, the people of Sylhet hailing from different ages, profession and political beliefs and united under the aegis of North East Education Trust (NEET) with the spirit of spreading education of various levels and branches of knowledge, have put our efforts and hard earned resources to establish North East University Bangladesh in Sylhet. We, the people of Sylhet hailing from different ages, profession and political beliefs and united under the aegis of North East Education Trust (NEET) with the spirit of spreading education of various levels and branches of knowledge, have put our efforts and hard earned resources to establish North East University Bangladesh in Sylhet. We, the people of Sylhet hailing from different ages, profession and political beliefs and united under the aegis of North East Education Trust (NEET) with the spirit of spreading education of various levels and branches of knowledge, have put our efforts and hard earned resources to establish North East University Bangladesh in Sylhet. \r\n\r\nNorth East Education Trust (NEET) and its members have the experience of running and managing educational institutions at the Primary, Secondary and Higher Secondary level and also a Medical College offering MBBS degree. Taking stock of the experience and also resources, we started thinking of establishing North East University Bangladesh in July 2012 and got approval of the Government and UGC in March 2012.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe University became functional with academic activities in July 2012 - Summer Semester. The Syndicate, Academic Council and other committees comprising renowned Scientists, Economists, Educationists and Professors have been guiding the University Management Team led by Professor Dr. M. Khalilur Rahman as Vice Chancellor since May 2012. The Trustees are grateful to Professor Dr. M. Sodoruddin Ahmed Chowdhury, the first Vice Chancellor of SUST, Late Professor Dr. Bazlul Mabin Chowdhury, Former Vice Chancellor, IUB, Professor Dr. Mohammed Farashuddin, Forme', 'ne ch.jpg', 'Professor Atful Hye Shibly, M.A, Ph.D', 'I feel great pleasure in expressing my heartiest congratulations and best wishes for the gradual but steady development of the North East University Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nSince its establishment four years back it has opened up great opportunities to play its role as one of the excellent universities of the country, especially in Sylhet.\r\n\r\nAs one who was closely associated at the time of its inception, I strongly feel that the NEUB has meanwhile fulfilled the expectations of its founders. Now time has come for the university with its academic experience and resources to look forward to further its activities and become the leader in the field of higher quality education in this part of the country. NEUB is determined and promised-bound to keep the good reputation of quality and high standard education in the academic arena of Bangladesh.\r\n\r\nI sincerely hope and strongly believe that our experienced and well qualified teachers teach to the best of their ability, guiding our young generation on a path for the sustainable acquisition of skills necessary for a great and productive future in this university.\r\n\r\nI wish all successes, prosperity and welfare of North East University Bangladesh', 'ne vc.jpg'),
(68, 62, 'Fareast International University', 'FIU', 'Prof. Dr. Nazmul Karim Chowdhury', '7 Rd No. 4, Dhaka1212', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E0%A6%AB%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B2+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B0+%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A5%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF+%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0/@23.7913601,90.40145', 'FIU_Logo.png', 'faaaaa.jpg', 'Sheikh Kabir Hossain   Chairman', 'Mr. Sheikh Kabir Hossain born in SHEIKH family of Tungipara, Gopalgonj. His father Late Shiekh Mosharraf Hossain was a Member of the Legislative Assembly.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nM. A. from Dhaka University. Served Government office, Bank, Corporation & resigned from  service in the year 1982 and started business.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPresently he is the Chairman of Association of Private Universities of Bangladesh (APUB), Regent-Board Member of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Science and Technology University (BSMRSTU), Chairman of Central Depository Bangladesh Limited (CDBL), Chairman of Sonar Bangla Insurance Limited, Sonarbangla Capital Management Ltd. (Merchant Bank), Health and Education for the Local Under Privileged People (HELP); Managing Director, Kabico Limited and Managing Partner of a Chinese Restaurant.\r\n\r\n\r\nPresently Chairman, Bangladesh Insurance Association (BIA); Member, Jatir Janak Bangbandhu Sheikh Mojibur Rahman Trustee Board; Board of Governors of Bangladesh Open University; Vice Chairman, Islamia Eye Hospital & Ispahani Eye Institute; Member, Dhaka Club Limited;  Golf Club, Kurmitola, Baridhara Cosmopolitan Club; Dhanmondi Club Limited; Honorary Member, Uttara Club Limited.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nHe is the Founder of various educational institutions in the locality.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nFormer Chairman, Bangladesh Red Crescent Society; Former Board of Governors of Bangladesh Privatization Commission (BPC); Former Director, Dhaka Stock Exchange Ltd.; Founder Chairman of Holy Family Red Crescent Medical College & Hospital, Dhaka.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nLife member, Bangladesh Andha Kalyan Samity, Bangladesh Family Planning Association and Bangladesh Lions Foundation.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nDistrict Governor of Lions District 315B1, Bangladesh. Elected International Director for the term 2005-2007 of Lions Clubs International. He obtained number of awards from Lions Clubs International and also obtained Sher-E-Bangla Gold Medal-2000 for Shamaj Sheba (Service to Society) from Bangla Youth Forum. Desh Bandhu Gold Med', 'faaaa ch.jpg', 'Prof. Dr. Nazmul Karim Chowdhury', 'Human being is the change-maker of the civilizations. Wisdom, experience, observation and critical thinking are the effective means of changes toward development seeded to quality education. The Fareast International University (FIU), by vision and mission cherishes and pursues the higher quality education with academic excellence to produce world class skillful manpower and human resources where knowledge is preserved, synthesized and disseminated towards higher quality education with academic excellence to produce world class skillful manpower and human resources who will accept the challenges of global corporate world. \r\n\r\nThe Government of the Peoples Republic of Bangladesh approved FIU on 15 September 2013 and the University Grants Commission of Bangladesh endorsed it on 06 October in the same year. It has started the academic functional operations from January 2014 (Spring Semester). FIU is currently operating trimester basis in 16 graduate and masters programs under the faculty of Business Administration, Engineering, Science, Liberal Arts & Social Sciences and LAW. FIU introduces international standard course curricula approved by the UGC of Bangladesh targeting to compete in the greater corporate world. Besides, there are different clubs and houses for Debate, English Language, Indoor-games, Cultural practices, and sports facilities for the benefit of our learners. It has research and academic collaborations with number of foreign universities. It is the first private university in Bangladesh selected by the government to offer MBA major in Project Monitoring and Evaluation. Moreover, FIU has established \"Integrated Research Institute for Inclusive Development (IRIID)\" for action research on various issues of the contemporary world and appropriate technology transfer for sustainable development.\r\n\r\nFIU has engaged renowned teaching figures as full time and adjunct faculty members for maintaining academic excellence. Administrative functionaries are exper', 'faaaa vc.jpg'),
(69, 63, 'University of South Asia', 'USA', 'Prof. M. A. Wadud Mondal ', 'House 78, Road 14, Block B, Banani, Dhaka, Bangladesh', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF+%E0%A6%85%E0%A6%AC+%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A5+%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BC%E0%A6%BE/@23.7948275,90.4027071,21z/data=!4m12!1m6!3m5!1s0x3755c711d77bc47b:0x90298e50635daf6a!2z4KaH4KaJ4Kao4Ka_4Kat4Ka-4Kaw4KeN4Ka44Ka_4Kaf4Ka_IOCmheCmrCDgprjgpr7gpongpqUg4KaP4Ka24Ka_4Kav4Ka84Ka-!8m2!3d23.7947944!4d90.4028312!3m4!1s0x3755c711d77bc47b:0x', 'usa.jpg', 'us.jpg', 'Prof. Dr. Mohammad Muhit', 'University of South Asia is committed to academic excellence in our classrooms; relevant programs in our curriculum; and caring, personal attention to our students. One of our great strengths is the enthusiastic, personal involvement of our trustees, administrators, faculty, staff, and alumni in creating a sense of community. We believe that the opportunity for higher education should be available to all who seek it, and we will continue to meet the ongoing challenges that higher education presents in the years ahead.\r\n\r\nOur students are provided with the academic tools, practical skills, and real world opportunities necessary to advance as leaders in their professions and their communities. We encourage active participation in an education that challenges critical thinking, provides career preparation, instills values, and inspires lifelong learning. We realize that each student is unique and, as a community, we strive to maximize that unique potential.', 'usa ch.jpg', 'Prof. M. A. Wadud Mondal ', 'The University of South Asia is drawn together by its commitment to a set of core values, including Inclusiveness, integrity, honesty, respect for others, personal accountability, contributing to the community and a dedication to excellence-qualities that play a key role in developing the teamwork and sound judgment that are central to our educational mission.', 'usa vc.jpg'),
(70, 64, 'Sonargaon University', 'SU', 'Professor M.A. Razzaque', ' JA-146, Wireless Gate, Mohakhali, Dhaka.', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%97%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%81%E0%A6%93+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF/@23.7524097,90.387428,21z/data=!4m12!1m6!3m5!1s0x3755b89829a023bf:0x4a7ebbfe5db5e4f6!2z4Ka44KeL4Kao4Ka-4Kaw4KaX4Ka-4KaB4KaTIOCmh-CmieCmqOCmv-CmreCmvuCmsOCnjeCmuOCmv-Cmn-Cmvw!8m2!3d23.7523858!4d90.38754!3m4!1s0x3755b89829a023bf:0x4a7ebbfe5db5e4f6!8m2!3d23.7523858!4d90.38754', 'SU-2.png', 'dfz.PNG', 'Professor M.A Razzaque', ' In the concluding statement, I would like to wish Sonargaon University all the best and hope that I would be able to put in my experience, knowledge and expertise to further support the growth of this promising institution. ', 'snnn ch.jpg', 'Md. Al Amin Molla', ' I wish every success of all students in their educational and professional pursuits. I hope that after getting education at SU, you will become an asset for the country and you will be able to play an important role in development of Bangladesh', 'snnnnn vc.jpg'),
(71, 65, 'IBAIS University', 'IBAIS', 'Mr. Aziz Al Mahmood', 'Dhanmondi., Road No.16, Dhaka 1209', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B8+%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF/@23.7543298,90.3723979,21z/data=!4m12!1m6!3m5!1s0x3755bf530767f4cb:0x5a26d785b702369f!2z4KaH4Kas4Ka-4KaH4Ka4IOCmh-CmieCmqOCmv-CmreCmvuCmsOCnjeCmuOCmv-Cmn-Cmvw!8m2!3d23.7544577!4d90.3725509!3m4!1s0x3755bf530767f4cb:0x5a26d785b702369f!8m2!3d23.7544577!4d90.3725509', 'download.jfif', 'IBAIS-University-2.jpg', 'Showkat Aziz (Russell)', 'Tolook back over our shoulder, IBAIS University was established in 2002 as an enterprise of IBAIS Limited, a Joint Stock Company, registered under the Company Act. In more than a decade, we have come a long way and we can be proud of our achievements. The full potentials however could not be exploited.\r\nIn the meantime, IBAIS University Trust has been established in line with the Private University Act 2010. The University has attained a new height under the dynamic leadership of professional Trustees. As required by the UGC, the management is taking effective measures to establish the University at its own land. We sincerely adhere to the Private University Act and the UGC rules and regulations to ensure professional conduct of the University affairs.\r\n\r\nLocated at the heart of Dhaka Metropolis, our University boasts of an array of renowned and resourceful teachers with unique academic background. Committed to quality education, IBAISU is a habitat of excellent academic environment. Our well-designed programs have opened a new vista of higher education to the learners to lead them to the most enviable position in life. All the departments of IBAIS University are unique in providing the best education through modern teaching methods.\r\n\r\nLike other facilities, the University library is also full of latest books and journals. Teachers and students are found to swarm around the library spending hours together. Our Labs are equipped with latest facilities to meet the demand of the teachers and the students.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the world of IBAIS University. We are all set to make a history and march ahead to a still brighter level of success.', 'ibais ch.jpg', 'Mohammed Ahsan Ullah', 'IBAIS University, Dhanmondi, Dhaka organized a Seminar on Bangladesh-India Joint Promotion of Tourism on 12/01/2019 at the IBAISU Campus.Mr. Md. Tofazzal Hossain Jewel , Member, BOT, IBAIS University Trust was the Chief Guest and Mr. Ajit Kumar Paul, President Tour Operators Forum attended the Seminar as the Special Guest Mr. Nyzrul Eslam Lenin, Chairman ,ITC was the Keynote Speaker. The function was presided over by Prof. M. Ahsan Ullah, Treasurer & VC (Officiating) .Senior Professionals and tourism industry leaders including Mr. Zamiul Ahmed, Member, BTB were present.\r\n\r\n', 'ibais vc.jpg');
